{
  "stem": "19807.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I remember my mother saying that the black pickup-- if the black pickup, which was covered, would pass through the street, they knew that they had somebody that black-- black pickup to be hung.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So, my father, because he had friends in any party of the Bulgarian government, did not want to get involved in one particular party, not to incur neither the wrath or to incur the displeasure of-- of friends that he grew up with.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So rather than do that, he moved to Plovdiv, which is the second largest city in Bulgaria.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And that's where my family on my mother's side resided.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "On my mother's side, they were very, very fine, more of the scholarly type people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My-- one of my uncles was the first chairman of the board of the bank of-- Franco-Bulgarian Bank.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Now, that was-- if you-- have to understand, that was in Bulgaria.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And that was in the 1930s.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And it was a very, very coveted position.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "In fact, some of the resentment on my father's side was that I was not in that city as the nephew of David, rather than the son of Moses.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But my other uncle was a businessman.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He had properties.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He had a hotel there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "He had a-- a store for men's clothing, the finest, on the main street.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "He had several houses.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And my youngest uncle, which was really my-- my favorite uncle on my mother's side, he was a pharmacist.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And he, finally, when he got his own pharmacy, then the-- the Nazis came.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And then it really broke his heart that they had to confiscate his pharmacy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Moses, but they called him Moshe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, his grandfather gave him an Arabic name, Turkish name, which called him Musa.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
